place.name: WITHYPOOL
place.gazetteerText: WITHYPOOLE, a parish, with a village, in the district of Tiverton and county of Somerset; adjoining Exmoor forest, 11 miles NW of Bampton r. station. Post town, Exford, under Taunton. Acres, 3,630. Real property, £1,797. Pop., 307. Houses, 60. The property is subdivided. The living is a p. curacy, annexed to Hawkridge. The church is early English. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
